&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Static site generators are a really great way to share public data. There are many advantages to this style of website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="advantages"&gt;Advantages
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fast loading and clean repeatable designs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content entry is done using Markdown, so there is nothing to break&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Site automatically updates when content is modified on the coresponding github repo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run for free with Github Pages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="dis-advantages"&gt;Dis-Advantages
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No dynamic content, like user accounts or logins. Displays content only&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designed for mainly text content, dynamic content is not easily buildable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Themes are typically not too flashy, but this could change in the future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content is designed to be 100% public&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
